cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper discusses bibliometric measures and the structure of partition cells formed by intersecting fixed subject categories in a database to approximate a scientist's specialty. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, given the focus on bibliometrics and publication records, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
